verbose_text: All cases from 2001 to 2011 with ASA concentrations> 30 mg/dL were reviewed for proximal tubule renal dysfunction (either elevation of creatinine on presentation that resolved prior to discharge or development of an elevation during hospital stay), an associated glucosuria (within the renal threshold level of 160-180 mg/dL or greater than expected based on serum glucose levels), and proteinuria.
